      "rowSpan": "1"
    }
  },
  {
    "id": "session-31-don-t-let-this-drag-on_summary",
    "type": "text",
    "props": {
      "content": "It was time to follow a dwarven map into the Vanapur Mountains in search of a hidden treasure trove that could fund their future ambitions. Their exploration uncovered a sealed dwarven fortress haunted by the legacy of Mornok the Flayer, where constructs, traps, and restless guardians still enforced ancient defenses. As they pushed deeper, the danger escalated with a brutal clash against a white dragon Presagiath that nearly claimed multiple lives. The session ended when the party breached the inner tomb, triggering hostile wards that divided them and leaving the true cost of disturbing the fortress yet to be revealed.",
      "col": "1",
      "row": "19",
      "colSpan": "1",
      "rowSpan": "1"
    }
  },
